column4: These are two Word files, with different versions of the same book chapter - so version3 was created from version2 (making a copy and then editing it)
Some of the elements of the excel file are used as input for the script in the terminal.
Copy elements from one xml to the other.
Not totally sure - both files resulted from a script (as edited in the terminal) - it is possible that I wanted to compare them.
First file is a citation. Second file is the papers proof (camera-ready). The citation was missing in the proof and had to be added.
Weak relationship. Notes about creating a trailer; and the outcome: the trailer created in the video editing software (final outcome).
Write script in the terminal -- outcome is the .xml file.
A draft for a book chapter, and a proposal for a presentation at a conference, both about the same topic.

The document captures some notes taken during a meeting about a trailer that I was in the process of creating. The second file, a video, is a capture of a video that I was using in the overarching task (in a video editor). So, there is some relationship between the two documents.
